🧠 How It Works
1. TF-IDF Vectorization
Term Frequency-Inverse Document Frequency gives higher weight to skills that are rare across all job roles.

text
TF-IDF = Term Frequency × log(Total Jobs / Jobs containing skill)
2. Cosine Similarity
Measures the angle between user skill vector and job role vector:

text
Similarity = (A · B) / (||A|| × ||B||)
1.0 = Perfect match

0.5 = Partial match

0.0 = No match

3. Content-Based Filtering
Unlike collaborative filtering (which uses other users' behavior), this system recommends based solely on item attributes (skills required for each job role).

